<TEXT>
ho chong who headed the south korean 
government as acting president in 1960 died at his home sunday 
following a long illness family members said he was 92 
the family said monday that ho will be buried on tuesday at the 
national cemetery on the southern bank of the han river which runs 
through this capital 
he is survived by one son and one daughter 
ho was an independence fighter against japanese colonial rule 
he headed south koreas caretaker government in 1960 following the 
ouster of the late president syngman rhee in a studentled uprising 
for democracy 
