denny bungarz knew he 
wanted to be a forest ranger from age 11 when his family camped in 
northern california in the 1940s to escape a polio scare 
he achieved that goal and 42 years later he ended up being the 
fire boss who protected the historic old faithful lodge from the 
firestorm that has engulfed yellowstone national park the 
countrys oldest national park 
letting that burn would have been an end to everybodys 
career starting with mine said bungarz who works in the 
mendocino national forest in northern california australia 
wouldnt have been far enough away for us 
bungarz 53 became a local celebrity as he appeared regularly 
on national news broadcasts during the wild days of early 
september when the north fork fire attacked the old faithful area 
with 400foot flames 
that came only several days after the fire roared toward the 
montana community of west yellowstone on the outskirts of the park 
protecting those areas with the loss of some cabins at old 
faithful was one of the few successes of firefighters battling the 
335500acre blaze 
